1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
We are going to try and answer the question, what is the difference between the block editor and the Site Editor?

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:10,000
We will compare the block editor and the Site Editor as well as explore the Site Editor tools.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
And by the end, we'll feel confident in using both things together to create our entire site layout.

4
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Without further ado, let's begin.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Site editing allows you the freedom to build every aspect of your WordPress site, from the header all the way down to the footer, using the power of blocks within the Site Editor feature.

6
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:38,000
But what is the Site Editor?

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:40,000
How does it differ from the block editor that we are used to?

8
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,000
How can we use templates in the Site Editor to create our overall structure?

9
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
To answer these burning questions, let's take a trip through our dashboard and compare the two.

10
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,000
The block editor is the foundation of your site's content and is used to add content to pages and posts.

11
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Let's refresh ourselves on how to add page and post content.

12
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
In your dashboard, head to pages if you are creating a static page, or go to posts for dynamic content such as a blog post.

13
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
When you click on "Add New", you will create content for that specific page or post.

14
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Compared to this, what does the Site Editor allow us to do exactly?

15
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
The Site Editor allows us to edit our site cohesively.

16
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Pages and posts are only used to add static or dynamic content using blocks.

17
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
On the other hand, the Site Editor uses blocks to create the overall look and feel of your site using templates.

18
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
But it also allows us to add and edit pages to ensure a seamless site editing experience.

19
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,000
If you've installed the block theme like Twenty Twenty-Four, access the Site Editor via Appearance and then click on "Editor".

20
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
The Site Editor loads your site's front page for editing.

21
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
On the left, there's the site view sidebar.

22
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
This tool lets you toggle between the key parts of your site, navigation, styles, pages, templates and patterns.

23
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Let's start with navigation.

24
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Here you can quickly see and tweak all your menus.

25
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
You can rename them, rearrange menu items etc.

26
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
When you click on Styles, you have the ability to change the style combination of your theme.

27
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:42,000
And when you click on Edit Styles, you can change your entire site's typography, colors and layout.

28
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,000
If you look down further below, you also have the option to customize the appearance of specific blocks for your whole site.

29
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:03,000
To see how these blocks will change if you edit them, go to your site's Style Book.

30
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:08,000
As mentioned, here you can preview any changes made.

31
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Below pages, you also have the option to create and edit pages, the same as when you are in the dashboard.

32
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,000
This feature allows you to stay in the Site Editor when editing your site or content on a page.

33
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,000
When working inside a page in the Site Editor, we add content to the Content block.

34
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Next, we'll make our way to patterns.

35
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Below patterns, we have access to a library of patterns.

36
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
We will be able to create and manage our own patterns.

37
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
We can view the patterns provided by our theme.

38
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,000
And then we can also create and manage template parts.

39
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,000
A quick note on template parts.

40
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
These are reusable groups of blocks that you can use to create repeated parts of your template, like the header and footer.

41
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
But now, let's focus on templates.

42
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:21,000
When we open templates, let's take a look at the top menu and run through what these elements allow you to do.

43
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,000
The plus icon or Inserter top left allows you to add any block or a pattern of blocks to any template you are working on.

44
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Next to your Inserter, you have the undo and the redo button.

45
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Next is the list view. This is a super useful tool that allows you to see a list of all the blocks that are on your page.

46
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:52,000
This is great for seeing your page's structure, as well as editing, moving and removing blocks.

47
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
In the middle at the top is the name of the template.

48
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
When you click on the preview button, you will be able to see what your site will look like with the changes applied.

49
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:13,000
On desktop, tablet or mobile.

50
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:16,000
And then, if you click on save, you can save changes.

51
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Next, the settings tab lets you display or hide the template and block settings sidebar.

52
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:28,000
So, when you select a block for example, you can use the settings sidebar to style the block further.

53
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Next to the settings tab, you've got the styles tab, which is another place where you can access your style settings.

54
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,000
And finally, if you click on the three vertical dots, you've got access to more options, such as selecting the spotlight mode, etc.

55
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Now we've had a brief rundown of the menu options.

56
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Let's take a closer look at templates.

57
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
At the top, it says "Express the layout of your site with templates".

58
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Templates use blocks in order to create the overall design of your site by adding a header, footer or even sidebar.

59
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:13,000
We can see all three at play when we open the page of the sidebar template.

60
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:17,000
We can see the structure being provided by the header, the sidebar and the footer.

61
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Please also note, templates can be applied to a single page or multiple pages.

62
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
With that in mind, let's say we want to add the template that's applied to our pages, for example.

63
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
There are a few options provided by our theme here, for example the default page template or the page with wide image.

64
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,000
But let's choose the page with no title.

65
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:50,000
When the template loads, you'll see an example of what this template looks like without any content.

66
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Here is where the list view comes in really handy. The sidebar on the left will show you how the blocks that make up this template are structured.

67
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Here you can see the components that make up this page template. The header is clearly marked when you click on it, as is the footer.

68
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:14,000
In the middle, you'll see a Group block that contains a Post Content block within it. This is super important.

69
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:21,000
The Content block is what allows the content of your page or post to appear in this template.

70
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Think of this block as the container for whatever you wrote in your pages or posts section.

71
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Without a container, your page content won't have anywhere to be displayed. So remember, we don't add content to templates.

72
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:41,000
We only modify our header and footer or sidebar.

73
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Let's go ahead and replace this header with a different header pattern that comes with our theme.

74
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:54,000
We can scroll through the available options.

75
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Then I will go ahead and select the centered header with logo pattern.

76
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:03,000
I will also select one of my existing navigation menus named Lifestyle.

77
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Once selected, we can go ahead and save.

78
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:21,000
Awesome, the page template is saved. But how do we add this template to a page?

79
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,000
For that, we can navigate back to our main dashboard and go to pages.

80
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,000
Then, click on the page you'd like to apply this template to. In your sidebar to the right, you'll see a template header.

81
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
Go ahead and click on that. This drop-down menu lists all of the templates you currently have saved.

82
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:50,000
In this case, let's select page with no title. And then we can update.

83
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:56,000
Here's how the page looks like with the default page template.

84
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,000
And here it is with the page with no title template applied.

85
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:09,000
You can repeat this for as many pages as you like and the same applies to your posts.

86
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,000
As you have seen, the block editor and the Site Editor work hand in hand.

87
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,000
The block editor only allows us to add content to pages and posts.

88
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:25,000
But the Site Editor gives you the ability to edit your site cohesively.

89
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,000
You can edit the look and feel, modify templates as well as add content to pages.

